ptensor provides CMake targets:

    find_package(ptensor CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE ptensor::ptensor)

Basic usage:

```cpp
#include <ptensor/tensor.hpp>
#include <ptensor/dtype.hpp>

using namespace p10;

int main() {
    // Create a tensor with specific dtype
    auto dtype = Dtype::from<float>();
    auto shape = make_shape({2, 3, 4});
    
    if (shape.is_ok()) {
        auto tensor = Tensor::zeros(dtype, shape.value());
        // Use tensor...
    }
    
    return 0;
}
```

Features:
- Core tensor operations with type-safe data type handling

Optional I/O support (enable with feature "io"):
- Image loading and saving
- NumPy file format support